#: ../../rma/rma.rst:8
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:10
msgid ""
"A return merchandise authorization (RMA) is a part of the process of "
"returning a product to receive a refund, replacement during the product's"
" warranty period."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:15
msgid "Configurations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:17
msgid ""
"The user is supposed to enable the configuration of Lot & serial numbers "
"from :menuselection:`Inventory --> Configuration --> Settings`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:20
msgid "Mark the checkbox labeled as **Lot & Serial Numbers**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:25
msgid ""
"Though the Lot & Serial Number is not enabled, the workflow will work the"
" same. Only product Lot & serial will not be in the picture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:29
msgid ""
"The initial flow of the RMA is common, i.e., Creating SO, confirming Sale"
" order and creating delivery orders. To refer Sale Order, refer the "
"following document."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:33 ../../rma/rma.rst:94
msgid ":doc:`../../sales`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:36
msgid "How to return the product"
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:38
msgid ""
"As mentioned above, to demonstrate the flow, there should be a completely"
" processed SO. To create RMA, goto :menuselection:`Sales --> RMA --> RMA "
"Request`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:43
msgid ""
"Select an SO for which the customer wants to create RMA request. Picking "
"number which refers to the selected SO. Select the request type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:46
msgid "The request date should be less than the product expiry date."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:50
msgid ""
"We have two Lot of the same product with expiry date 10/02/2018 and "
"10/31/2018 respectively."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:53
msgid ""
"If the customer is trying to return the product which is already expired,"
" then the system will not allow to proceed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:56
msgid "The warning will be generated while confirming the RMA request."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:60
msgid ""
"Here the expiry date of the first lot is less than the date of RMA "
"request, that means, some of the products are not eligible for returning."
" So the customer is able to return the number of product which is "
"mentioned in the above warning. To proceed, update the number of quantity"
" of product in RMA request."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:65
msgid ""
"Once the user clicks on **Create RMA** button, the pop up will open to "
"ask if the user wants refund. Once the RMA is created, product picking "
"will be generated, where the user has to update the quantity of the "
"product under Operations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:71
msgid ""
"Once the Stock Picking is validated, the product will be returned and the"
" product quantity will be increased with returned product quantity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:75
msgid "How to replace the product"
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:77
msgid ""
"The workflow remains the same unto creating the RMA request. The main "
"difference is that, there is a checkbox labeled as **Replacement?** which"
" is mandatory to mark for replacement."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:82
msgid ""
"Once the RMA request is processed, the user has to Click over the "
"**Return** button, which will further create an **Outgoing Stock "
"Picking**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:87
msgid ""
"Once the Outgoing Stock Picking is validate, the product is Replaced "
"successfully."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:90
msgid "How to work with Web RMA"
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:92
msgid "Creating SO from the Web is already defined in Sales Document."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:96
msgid "Open up the Sale Order which is completely processed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:100
msgid ""
"The user will be able to see a button labeled as **Return/Replace**. By "
"clicking over that button, a pop up will open for returning or replacing "
"the product. The user is supposed to key in the quantity and reason of "
"the process. If the user wants to replace then mark the checkbox labeled "
"as **Replacement?**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:107
msgid ""
"Now, to the backend, there will be an RMA generated related to the "
"particular SO. Confirm the RMA. While creating the RMA, a pop up will "
"open where user has to select **Picking Type**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rma/rma.rst:112
msgid ""
"Once the RMA is created, it will create a Stock Picking which is to be "
"validated further and product is returned/replaced successfully."
msgstr ""

